cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper is about improving the scalability of dictionary-based classifiers for time series classification. The primary focus is on the BOSS algorithm, which is an ensemble-based approach that captures the frequency of pattern occurrences in a time series. The paper proposes a modification to the BOSS algorithm that replaces its parameter search with random selection, which allows for easy implementation of contracting and check-pointing. The paper also tests the application of common ensembling techniques to help retain accuracy from the loss of the BOSS parameter search. Given these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), but to a lesser extent.
